SIMPLE: woolen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Woolen
<hw>Wool"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wollen</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>wyllen</ets>. See <er>Wool</er>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>woollen</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of wool; consisting of wool; <as>as,
<ex>woolen</ex> goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to wool or woolen cloths; <as>as,
<ex>woolen</ex> manufactures; a <ex>woolen</ex> mill; a <ex>woolen</ex>
draper.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Woolen scribbler</b></col>, <cd>a machine for combing or
preparing wool in thin, downy, translucent layers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woolen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Woolen
<hw>Wool"en</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>woollen</ets>.]</ety> <def>Cloth made of wool; woollen
goods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woolenet</ent>⟦br⟧
